# Configuration via pydantic-settings

Never use `os.getenv()` or `os.environ` in `app/` modules.

All config flows through `Settings(BaseSettings)` in `app/settings.py`. Inject via `SettingsDep` / `get_settings()` in dependencies — not direct imports in route bodies.

Why: one typed, validated source of truth; testable via env monkeypatch + `get_settings.cache_clear()`.

Note: the no-default-args project rule applies to **function parameters**, not Pydantic model fields on `Settings`.
